Filling:
    6 medium apples
    1/3 cup packed brown sugar
    1 tbsp cornstarch
    1 tbsp lemon juice
    1/2 tsp vanilla extract
    1 tsp ground cinnamon
    1/2 tsp ground cloves
    pinch of salt

Batter:
    1-1/2 cup flour
    1-1/2 cup sugar
    3 tsp baking powder
    1/2 tsp salt
    1 cup milk
    8 tbsp melted butter

Dice apples into saucepan and add remaining filling ingredients. Cook a few minutes to thicken.

Mix batter ingredients until just combined.

Pour filling mixture into greased third pan or 9x13.  Add 1/3 of batter mixture and loosely incorporate.

Cover the mixture evenly with remaining batter.

Bake in a greased third pan (or 9x13) at 175/350 for 40 minutes.